<p>If the userâ€™s device has <strong>bold text enabled</strong> there are certain parts of the system that will automatically respond to that. For example, if you are using a <strong>default navigation controller</strong> in your app, <strong>the title and the UIBarButtonItem at the top of the screen will become bold.</strong> </p>  <p>How can I <strong>disable</strong> the effect of <strong>bold text</strong> to <strong><em>all my app</em></strong> and specially to the default navigation controller ( to the <strong>title</strong> and the <strong>UIBarButtonItem</strong> ) in my app ? - <strong>swift 2.0</strong> ( <strong>iOS 8 &amp; 9</strong> ) . thx all : )</p>  <p>I have this code to detect if the bold text is enabled : (<strong>if it is useful</strong>)</p>  <pre><code> if (UIAccessibilityIsBoldTextEnabled()) { // use bold font         }  else {      // use standard font } </code></pre>